social_posts.post_text: I’ve had my degree for 2 1/2 years, but today I finally got to “graduate” 🎓🎉 #berklee2020

Last Christmas you gave me your heart, but the very next day, you gave it away…. This year, so save me from tears, you can come to my gig at Speakeasy in Newport tonight 🙌😝 It’s my last solo gig of the season, and I’ll be there 10-1! Xmas songs may or may not be included in the set 🎄

It’s been a lazy Friday afternoon with my favorite 6/7 stringed and 4 legged friends, but unfortunately kitty snuggles have to pause for my last couple shows before heading back home to OK for Christmas!

Tonight! I’ll be shipping up to Boston (well Cambridge) for some last minute acoustic jams at the Middle East Corner 10-1! 

Tomorrow, catch the lads and I in the @davealvesmusic Band rockin it at Mayflower Brewing in Plymouth following their Punk Rock Market! We’ll be there 4-7pm! 

See you guys out there! 🤘

Going back to Tulsa one more time,
I've got home sweet Oklahoma on my mind 🎵

#leonrussel #tulsa #tulsastudiorow #churchstudio #tulsaoklahoma #oklahoma #music #guitar
Last Gig of 2022 with some of my favorite people in the world 🤘Here’s to another epic year of music making, Happy New Year!!

Tonight, I was supposed to play up in Watertown, but due to unforeseen circumstances, the venue had to cancel. However! I decided that today would be a fun night for a livestream show (which I haven’t done since my senior recital). It will be a fun, chill night of some of my favorite acoustic arrangements and yes, I will be taking requests 🙃 Grab a drink and log on to Facebook 7-10pm est! (Link in bio) See you then! 

#live #facebooklive #livemusic #acoustic #unplugged #liveunplugged #guitar #guitarist #rock

Finally got my “Video Studio,” aka bedroom, at my new apartment in Providence set up for filming! After a loose hiatus (primarily due to my crazy gig schedule!), I’m excited to try and get back into the game of making videos/music content. To test-run everything, here’s some Britney Spears!

PS: Consider this a promise for more shred! What can I say, i’ve been i’ve been going through a singing phase. 

PSS: Speaking of gigs, come check out some unplugged jams THIS SUNDAY 1/22 at the Middle East Corner in Camrbidge! I’ll be there 9-12 (ish) 🎸

Wowza - Happy Friday! I have to say the last 7 days in the Millisaverse have been a bit of a fever dream…including but not limited to: the best poutine in RI, some powerful gin and tonics, way too little sleep, over loads of sleep, the most beautiful snowy mountains i’ve ever seen, a random guy insisting I give him hard drugs (I am not nor have ever been in possession of those), a busted tire AND side view mirror, a nasty sore throat, and some awesome gigs… in no particular order. 

Anyways, that’s my friday life update! Here’s a selfie just because AND to remind you to come rock out with me and the @davealvesmusic gang tonight at Hometown Tavern in Warren! 8:30-12 see you there! 🤘

Happy Friday, Friends 😄 

This is a rough “quiet-day-at-work” clip of an original. I started this work-in-progress a few weeks ago - it’s a complete rewrite of a (very terrible) song I wrote for one of my songwriting classes in college. I won’t bore you with the details, but it has a lot of personal meaning, and writing it has been a huge outlet to face thoughts and feelings I’ve been avoiding “dealing with” for over 3 years. Despite my inherent inability to write lyrics, putting it all on paper has been really healing (the power of music, eh?)

I don’t know if I’ll ever release a recorded version because it feels like a “live” song saved for intimate acoustic moments - but I will be “premiering” the whole song tonight at my show @interwoven, and I would genuinely love to see some familiar faces there 💙 

Anyways, TLDR: here’s a snippet of a mega personal song I wrote/am still working on, and I’m playing it tonight in New Bedford! Come through if you’re around!

Tomorrow I’ll be closing out my third year of teaching at Berklee’s Guitar Sessions program - every year, I’m continually impressed by the enormous amount of talent all of these students bring. Watching each of them grow as musicians and challenging themselves as guitarists is one of the most rewarding things I could ever ask for as an instructor ❤️ And of course; huge shout out to @kim.perlak, @gtrnerd, @janeomiller, @saldifusco, Earle Pughe, @nick.ats, @tanner.ats, and all of the other incredible faculty, staff, and work studies that make this happen every year 🙌

Onward to the next adventure: my first year as an instructor at Berklee’s Five-Week!

I’m absolutely gutted to hear about the untimely passing of @tallguitardave Dave Cohen.. Not only was he an incredible guitarist and luthier, he was a truly incredible person. When I first got my @eqguitars a few years ago, I was going through a particularly rough patch both career and life-wise, and every time I was in the shop, he would lend an ear and genuinely offer some of the best advice I’ve ever received. There’s no doubt that he left an incredible mark not only on the Boston Music/Metal scene but on the guitar world as a whole. Rest in Power, Dave; you will be truly missed.

Another amazing day of 5-Week, finished off with a double rainbow over the Pru 🌈 Happy Thursday! 🖤

Happy New Year’s Eve, wonderful internet friends! We’re ending an amazing run of Legally Blonde with @moonboxproductions this afternoon - huge shoutout to the rest of the band, cast, and crew - this show was a blast to play! Then tonight, I’ll be heading down to Newport with the @davealvesmusic band to ring in the new year at @viestesimplyitalian! 

I’ll make a better New Year’s compilation later, but as always, I’m eternally grateful for all of the wonderful people who continue to support me on my crazy music journey. If you’re free and around tonight, come have a drink and celebrate!
